Uses of Package
infotrader.parser.model

  • Packages that use infotrader.parser.model 
    Package Description
    infotrader.parser.model
    A data model for holding genealogical data.
    infotrader.parser.parser
    Classes for parsing GEDCOM-format data and constructing an object graph from it, using objects in the org.gedcom4j.model package.
    infotrader.parser.parser.event
    Classes for supporting Observer pattern during parse operations (which can be lengthy).
    infotrader.parser.query
    A package for classes that can help with common queries over the object model.
    infotrader.parser.validate
    Classes that can validate the data in the object model for a variety of problems, so that the data written by the Writer is compliant with the GEDCOM standard.
    infotrader.parser.writer
    Classes for writing GEDCOM files from the object model
    infotrader.sitedatastorage

    AbstractCitation
    An abstract base class for other source citations (both with and without source)
    AbstractElement

    Represents an address.
    AdoptedByWhichParent

    A date/time that a change was made.
    CharacterSet
    A character set.
    CitationData
    A class for source citation data.
    Corporation
    Represents a Corporation.
    EventRecorded
    A event that was recorded in a source.
    FileReference

    Header
    Header information about the GEDCOM file
    HeaderSourceData
    Information about the header source data.
    InfoTraderVersion
    Information about the version of the GEDCOM spec used
    Multimedia

    Repository

    A citation to a repository
    Source

    SourceCallNumber
    A source call number, used in { RepositoryCitation} classes.
    SourceData

    SourceSystem
    A source system.
    StringTree
    A structure to hold an element (as string data) from a GEDCOM file in such a way as to preserve and recognize the hierarchical structure of GEDCOMs (based on the level field of each line)
